d><td align=\"right\">4.06%</td></tr>\n<tr><td>日高養護学校高知みかづき分校</td><td align=\"right\">45</td><td align=\"right\">3.73%</td></tr>\n<tr><td>高知若草養護学校土佐希望の家分校</td><td align=\"right\">34</td><td align=\"right\">2.82%</td></tr>\n<tr><td>高知ろう学校</td><td align=\"right\">33</td><td align=\"right\">2.73%</td></tr>\n<tr><td>光の村養護学校土佐自然学園特別支援学校</td><td align=\"right\">29</td><td align=\"right\">2.40%</td></tr>\n<tr><td>高知大学教育学部附属特別支援学校</td><td align=\"right\">28</td><td align=\"right\">2.32%</td></tr>\n<tr><td>高知江の口養護学校高知大学医学部附属病院分校</td><td align=\"right\">5</td><td align=\"right\">0.41%</td></tr>\n</table>\n\n</details>\n\n### Attractions\n\n<details>\n<summary>水族館 (Aquariums) — 263 Visitors (0.09% of Total Demand)</summary>\n\n<table>\n<tr><th>Name</th><th align=\"right\">Annual Visitors</th><th align=\"right\">Modeled Demand</th><th align=\"right\">% of 水族館 Demand</th></tr>\n<tr><td>桂浜水族館</td><td align=\"right\">96,000</td><td align=\"right\">263</td><td align=\"right\">100.00%</td></tr>\n</table>\n\n</details>\n<details>\n<summary>動物園 (Zoos) — 1,367 Visitors (0.45% of Total Demand)</summary>\n\n<table>\n<tr><th>Name</th><th align=\"right\">Modeled Demand</th><th align=\"right\">% of 動物園 Demand</th></tr>\n<tr><td>わんぱーくこうちアニマルランド</td><td align=\"right\">851</td><td align=\"right\">62.25%</td></tr>\n<tr><td>高知県立のいち動物公園</td><td align=\"right\">516</td><td align=\"right\">37.75%</td></tr>\n</table>\n\n</details>\n<details>\n<summary>植物園 (Botanical Gardens) — 488 Visitors (0.16% of Total Demand)</summary>\n\n<table>\n<tr><th>Name</th><th align=\"right\">Modeled Demand</th><th align=\"right\">% of 植物園 Demand</th></tr>\n<tr><td>高知県立牧野植物園</td><td align=\"right\">488</td><td align=\"right\">100.00%</td></tr>\n</table>\n\n</details>\n\n## Methodology\n\nResident and commuter totals are derived from employed persons (就業者数) and workers (従業者数) per small census area (小地域), refined by 500m labor mesh and 250m/100m resident mesh to achieve sub-district point placement. Population counts are conserved at the 小地域 level, and point placement is optimized via a mesh-aware loss function.\n\nCommute patterns are modeled using a gravity model augmented by known origin-destination flows at the municipality (市町村) or designated city ward (区) level.\n\n## Data Sources\n\n- 令和2年国勢調査 (2020 National Census) — [e-Stat](https://www.e-stat.go.jp/)\n- 令和3年経済センサス (2021 Economic Census) — [e-Stat](https://www.e-stat.go.jp/)\n- 簡易100mメッシュ人口 (100m Mesh Population) — [GTFS-GIS](https://gtfs-gis.jp/teikyo/)\n- 国土数値情報 (National Land Numerical Information) — [MLIT](https://nlftp.mlit.go.jp/)\n- 空港管理状況調査 (Airport Management Statistics) — [MLIT Aviation](https://www.mlit.go.jp/koku/15_bf_000185.html)\n- 港湾調査 (Port Survey) — [MLIT Ports](https://www.mlit.go.jp/k-toukei/kouwan.html)\n- 大学ポートレート (University Portraits) — [JASSO](https://portraits.niad.ac.jp/)\n- 学校基本調査 (School Basic Survey) — [MEXT](https://www.mext.go.jp/)\n- 観光統計 (Tourism Statistics) — [JNTO](https://statistics.jnto.go.jp/)\n- Overture Maps Foundation — [Overture](https://overturemaps.org/)\n- 海しる / J-EGG500 (Ocean Information / Bathymetry) — [MSIL](https://www.msil.go.jp/) / [JODC](https://www.jodc.go.jp/)\n\n## License\n\nThis map data is released under the [MIT License](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).\n\n## Credits\n\nMap authored by [Yukina-](https://subwaybuildermodded.com/credits/)",
